SIMPLE: ticktack
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Ticktack
<hw>Tick"tack`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See <er>Tick</er>
to beat, to pat, and (for sense 2) cf. <er>Tricktrack</er>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>A noise like that made by a clock or a watch.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A kind of backgammon played both with men and pegs;
tricktrack.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A game at <qex>ticktack</qex> with words.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ticktack</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Ticktack
<hw>Tick"tack`</hw>, <pos>adv.</pos> <def>With a ticking noise, like
that of a watch.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ticpolonga</ent>⟦br⟧
